data.value: RA 8292 and it’s Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR) - An Act Providing For The Uniform Composition And Powers Of The Governing Boards, The Manner Of Appointment And Term Of Office Of The President Of Chartered State Universities And Colleges, And For Other Purposes.

data.name: label11.Text
data.value: General Mandate - The University shall primarily provide advanced education, higher technological, professional instruction and training in the fields of education, arts and sciences, public, administration, information technology, accountancy, law and other relevant fields of study. It shall also promote research and extension service, and provide progressive leadership in its areas of specialization.

data.value: RA 9456 – An Act Converting The Bukidnon State College In The City Of Malaybalay, Province Of Bukidnon, Into A State University, To Be Known As The Bukidnon State University And Appropriating Funds Therefor (Approved by the President of the Republic on May 15, 2007).

data.name: label13.Text
data.value: Bukidnon State University is committed to produce globally competitive and responsible graduates through excellent instruction, responsive research, sustainable extension and quality production for the highest satisfaction of its stakeholders.
